 of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Wiliam Skeffington was born in 1298, in Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Hugh Skeffington, was 31 and his mother, Mary Sweetenham, was 28. He had at least 1 son with Mary de Brickhull."},"et":{"1298–":"1298–Surnud","1298–Male":"1298–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1267–1312":"1267–1312","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1369":"1369","1312":"1312","1267":"1267","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1270":"1270","Bretton, Flintshire, Wales":"Bretton, Flintshire, Wales","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1298–":"1298–Kuollut","1298–Male":"1298–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1267–1312":"1267–1312","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1369":"1369","1312":"1312","1267":"1267","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","about 1330":"noin 1330","1270":"1270","Bretton, Flintshire, Wales":"Bretton, Flintshire, Wales","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1298–":"1298–Décédé","1298–Male":"1298–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1267–1312":"1267–1312","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1369":"1369","1312":"1312","1267":"1267","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","about 1330":"environ 1330","1270":"1270","Bretton, Flintshire, Wales":"Bretton, Fl